[root@VM_0_8_centos ~]# cat /proc/1/ns/
ipc   mnt   net   pid   user  uts 


1 kind namespace has multiple processes, 1 proc belongs to 1 kind namespace, there are 6 kinds of namespaces

file descriptor -> inode number -> inode -> description

To control limits of namespaces 
[root@VM_0_8_centos ~]# cat /proc/sys/user/max_
max_ipc_namespaces   max_mnt_namespaces   max_net_namespaces   max_pid_namespaces   max_user_namespaces  max_uts_namespaces

Compare user space, the kernel limit config is here
[root@VM_0_8_centos ~]# cat /proc/sys/kernel/threads-max
14532

Mount namespaces, All of the processes that reside in the same mount namespace will see the same view in these files
/proc/[pid]/mounts, /proc/[pid]/mountinfo, and /proc/[pid]/mountstats 
